title: Input, $$t$$
text: The input is $$t=30$$, so $$30$$ minutes after noon, which is equivalent to 12:30pm.

title: Output
text: $$f(t)=volume$$ of a tank of gasoline in gallons, so $$f(30)=volume$$ of a tank of gasoline in gallons at $$t=30$$

title: Explanation
text: At 12:30pm, the volume of the tank of gasoline is $$0$$ gallons. That is, at 12:30pm, the tank holds no gasoline.
